25|$|<b>Gaussian</b> <b>beam</b> {{propagation}} is {{a simple}} paraxial physical optics model for the propagation of coherent radiation such as laser beams. This technique partially accounts for diffraction, allowing accurate calculations of {{the rate at which}} a laser beam expands with distance, and the minimum size to which the beam can be focused. <b>Gaussian</b> <b>beam</b> propagation thus bridges the gap between geometric and physical optics.|$|E
